title: Keep an eye on directorys 
catalog: os/linux
agents: linux
author: Bastian Kuhn <mail@bastian-kuhn.de>
license: GPL
distribution: none
description:
 You can monitor the filesize of all configured directorys
 HINT: You have to setup the agent. He have to know the directory paths

perfdata:
 The actual size of the directory

item:
 The directory path

inventory:
 Automatic inventory is supported. You just have to configure the agent configuration file dir_size.cfg on
 the client site.

 dir_size.cfg just lists one directory per line.

 Warning and critical levels can be configured with check_parameters.
